No. Really travel.

00:23:28.801 --> 00:23:32.601
My coven has been meeting every Thursday, Saturday to prepare for a grand coracle journey,

00:23:32.602 --> 00:23:36.202
along the same route we took when our people came from Russia and Alaska along the bearing straight.

00:23:36.203 --> 00:23:37.403
What? A coracle?

00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:40.400
Oh, is that like a Mybachsu? Mmm. I prefer American cars.

00:23:40.401 --> 00:23:42.301
No. Coracle.

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:04.830
Cora means Arabian Gazelle, which we all know was the daughter of Zeus.

00:24:04.831 --> 00:24:07.831
And call means gather grass and sew it together.

00:24:07.832 --> 00:24:12.232
A coracle is a single-person rowing boat made of reeds and twigs from ancient Britain.

00:24:12.233 --> 00:24:17.033
There are so many wonderful things you can learn from the ancient Britains, Amy.

00:24:17.034 --> 00:24:21.534
Like metallurgy and how to cauterize the wound when a bear has eaten your arm.

00:24:21.535 --> 00:24:25.535
Everyone used to have a coracle, Amy, even people who were scared of water.

00:24:25.536 --> 00:24:30.536
We're all about working to preserve the diversity of natural life.

00:24:30.537 --> 00:24:32.037
We use everything.

00:24:32.038 --> 00:24:33.838
Question, who's this we?

00:24:33.839 --> 00:24:35.039
My coven.

00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:36.040
Like witches?

00:24:36.041 --> 00:24:39.841
No, yeah, yes, but not witches like you think.

00:24:39.842 --> 00:24:45.042
We're just a group of people who believe in communal sharing and chanting a lot and can't find husbands.

00:24:45.043 --> 00:24:51.543
Reading magazines, cloaks, wands, horned gods, rubbing your skin raw with rocks,

00:24:51.544 --> 00:24:56.544
dying of old age at 27, crying in terror when it starts to thunder.

00:24:56.545 --> 00:24:59.545
And these are all the things our ancestors did.

00:24:59.546 --> 00:25:02.546
Since I found my new mind and body, things have really changed for me.

00:25:02.547 --> 00:25:05.847
Our modern society only celebrates a select few.

00:25:05.848 --> 00:25:09.548
Every woman and every man is a star in the sky, Amy.

00:25:09.549 --> 00:25:12.549
Not just the ones that sing on TV or those people in the movies.

00:25:12.550 --> 00:25:17.550
I think I know what you need to separate your reflection from your true self.

00:25:17.551 --> 00:25:19.051
A Zen garden.

00:25:19.052 --> 00:25:22.552
Oh, my brother had one of those and the federales came.

00:25:22.553 --> 00:25:24.553
No, no, no, no, no. Zen.

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:30.810
silly girl.

00:25:31.270 --> 00:25:33.710
It's a little sandbox you draw pictures in.

00:25:33.990 --> 00:25:38.290
It teaches you things like that death isn't an end. It's just a stage and also a beginning of a new journey.

00:25:38.490 --> 00:25:40.490
Do you have a leader in this weirdo cult of yours?

00:25:40.491 --> 00:25:42.491
Not a cult, a coven. There's a big difference.

00:25:42.492 --> 00:25:44.332
Yes, our leader's name is Phil.

00:25:44.690 --> 00:25:47.170
That's a weird name for a leader of a group of witches.

00:25:47.171 --> 00:25:51.411
Oh, hi Phil. What hairy legs you've got? What with being a man who's a witch and everything.

00:25:51.412 --> 00:25:53.132
Do not disrespect Phil.

00:25:53.530 --> 00:25:58.210
He teaches us the wheel of the year, Amy. It's full of solar holidays and goes round and round and round.

00:25:58.211 --> 00:26:00.211
You can learn a lot from the sun and the moon.

00:26:00.450 --> 00:26:05.130
If you look at the sun for too long, you can go blind, meaning it is something to be respected.

00:26:05.410 --> 00:26:08.050
And the moon has a dark side, just like we do.

00:26:08.330 --> 00:26:12.010
And some people have craters and only a sixth of gravity.

00:26:12.370 --> 00:26:14.210
The ancient Britains knew the moon could breathe.

00:26:14.410 --> 00:26:16.810
We can change the world. We arrange the world.

00:26:17.090 --> 00:26:21.090
It's dying though, Amy, and it needs some mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

00:26:21.370 --> 00:26:23.810
Like a swan or a fish on a hook.

00:26:24.130 --> 00:26:29.410
If you take your nervous system seriously, if you take your organs seriously and explore them, some really neat things can happen.

00:26:29.411 --> 00:26:30.331
Phil taught us that.

00:26:30.570 --> 00:26:33.050
He's been to Mali to meet with the village elders.

00:26:33.051 --> 00:26:35.011
That's why there's the ceremony of the knife.

