00:44:34.401 --> 00:44:39.801
My next guest is the star of the hit show, Just the Five of Us, where he appears as the rich father of a family of misfits.

00:44:39.802 --> 00:44:43.802
But more recently, he's working on the controversial theater piece, In the future, there will be robots.

00:44:43.803 --> 00:44:46.003
Claude Maggin.

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:01.580
not. Welcome to the show.

00:45:02.400 --> 00:45:06.400
Thanks, Amy. However, you have mispronounced my name.

00:45:06.401 --> 00:45:11.301
It's Maj, which rhymes with badge, a as in duh, and no as in more than you.

00:45:11.302 --> 00:45:12.202
Majano.

00:45:12.203 --> 00:45:15.003
Anyway, thank you for having me on the show.

00:45:15.004 --> 00:45:17.604
It's always a pleasure to discuss my art.

00:45:17.605 --> 00:45:20.005
Yes. You're so funny.

00:45:20.006 --> 00:45:24.006
Now, Claude, you're an interesting man, if you don't mind me saying so myself.

00:45:24.007 --> 00:45:28.807
Because on the one hand, you're on the funniest show in the whole wide world, just the five of us.

00:45:28.808 --> 00:45:32.208
And on the other, you do those weird theater dance shows which aren't funny.

00:45:32.209 --> 00:45:35.209
Yes, thank you, technical school dropout.

00:45:35.210 --> 00:45:38.210
I'm sure sitting here talking all day is terribly difficult.

00:45:38.211 --> 00:45:39.611
Juliard is not.

00:45:39.612 --> 00:45:42.012
In the future, there will be robots is not a funny piece.

00:45:42.013 --> 00:45:48.813
It deals with the most important issues in the world today, love, pain, suffering, skin tight pants and well-stretched groin muscles.

00:45:48.814 --> 00:45:51.814
But see, music has no name, Amy.

00:45:51.815 --> 00:45:57.815
It's about depth and texture and sense of community that emerges from the struggle going on within all of us.

00:45:57.816 --> 00:46:01.816
Between man and machine, between the angel and the beast.

00:46:01.817 --> 00:46:06.817
It's as if Petrushka and Leonard Bernstein were in a ferocious dance competition with switch blades.

00:46:06.818 --> 00:46:09.018
That is passion, my dear.

00:46:09.019 --> 00:46:10.819
Um, okay.

00:46:10.820 --> 00:46:13.820
So it's a bit like just the five of us. What a show.

00:46:13.821 --> 00:46:17.821
I love Jimmy. He's so cute, even though he looks so young.

00:46:17.822 --> 00:46:20.022
I'd rather not talk about my complicated

00:46:30.000 --> 00:46:34.700
patients working with him. I'm a performer. I express myself any way I can.

00:46:34.701 --> 00:46:40.381
While I'd never attempt to describe just the five of us as anything other than worshipless pap,

00:46:40.382 --> 00:46:42.582
I need to support my serious art.

00:46:42.583 --> 00:46:45.783
It's like stealing a boom box to do live interpretive dance.

00:46:45.784 --> 00:46:50.484
If I bring joy to people's hearts doing an interpretation of a tree in the park, who is harmed?

00:46:50.485 --> 00:46:55.785
There is a value I derive from art, as a man, as a creator, and that is this.

00:46:55.786 --> 00:46:59.486
Never overestimate the dreadfulness of the mass market,

00:46:59.487 --> 00:47:03.787
the degrading excess of the culture, or the horrors that we all have within it.

00:47:04.300 --> 00:47:07.480
Great. Yeah. Um, me too.

00:47:07.481 --> 00:47:10.981
But as Mr. Chesterfield, you're so funny.

00:47:10.982 --> 00:47:16.702
What is it you say? Not in my house. That gets me every time.

00:47:16.703 --> 00:47:21.903
especially after the drunken tramp you adopted has wet himself. Oh, say it for me, please.

00:47:21.904 --> 00:47:24.904
As they say in France, Matrice.

00:47:24.905 --> 00:47:25.905
Please.

00:47:25.906 --> 00:47:30.506
Not in my house. Please, I came on your fine show to discuss art,

00:47:30.507 --> 00:47:36.007
not people that whore themselves out on the altar of commercial success, dancing like a puppet alongside a genetic freak.

00:47:36.008 --> 00:47:37.908
Although, I do that too.

00:47:38.200 --> 00:47:41.400
Okay, Moody. So, what do you want to talk about?

00:47:41.401 --> 00:47:45.401
Oh, I don't know. My performance at the Hollywood Bowl, perhaps.

00:47:45.402 --> 00:47:47.902
There are some that attend the concert inside.

00:47:47.903 --> 00:47:50.903
I am the concert outside myself.

00:47:50.904 --> 00:47:54.404
In the parking lot where we build bonfires and dance.

00:48:00.000 --> 00:48:02.300
It comes back to the seriousness of my purpose.

00:48:02.301 --> 00:48:07.101
At a young age, I held puppet shows on the corner that had people weeping and lying down in the streets.

00:48:07.102 --> 00:48:13.202
It's about movement, about encouraging ordinary working class people that there is something enervating about a modern dance performance.

00:48:13.203 --> 00:48:18.803
That seeing in the future there will be robots will change your life, no matter what your life's like now.

00:48:18.804 --> 00:48:20.604
Kind of like getting a new haircut.

00:48:20.605 --> 00:48:21.805
Yes, exactly.

00:48:21.806 --> 00:48:25.506
No, nothing like a new haircut, you halfwit.

00:48:25.507 --> 00:48:26.907
This is movement.

00:48:26.908 --> 00:48:29.408
Watch my hand. Yes, movement.

00:48:29.409 --> 00:48:33.809
There's a manatee on stage. See? He cannot hear from the wall of Wagner around him.

00:48:33.810 --> 00:48:39.410
We have lasers that shoot him down, cut him free, free his soul from the bondage of the past.

00:48:39.411 --> 00:48:44.811
And then on stage, we have snow that falls and represents love in all its forms.

00:48:44.812 --> 00:48:48.612
The robot makes a snow angel, and we begin to cry.

00:48:48.613 --> 00:48:50.913
Close curtain.

00:48:50.914 --> 00:48:52.914
Um, okay.

00:48:52.915 --> 00:48:56.215
Well, I've loved just the five of us.

00:48:56.216 --> 00:48:58.516
Please, please, please, enough.

00:48:58.517 --> 00:49:01.217
Five succeeds while robots starve.

00:49:01.218 --> 00:49:02.818
Attendance has been poor.

00:49:02.819 --> 00:49:09.919
If I were opening this with the Orchestra Filarmonica de Jalapa in Mexico, there would be riots in the streets with small children giving me flowers and weeping.

00:49:09.920 --> 00:49:15.820
Here in Vice City, they wouldn't know art unless it came as a tube of beef jerky.

00:49:15.821 --> 00:49:18.221
They told me, Claude, it can't be done.

00:49:18.222 --> 00:49:21.222
Vice City is for sun worshippers and Philistines.

00:49:30.000 --> 00:49:31.900
lines and I told them, no.

00:49:31.901 --> 00:49:37.201
I told them, if I'm directing a work of commercial dross down there, I must save my soul with some serious art.

00:49:37.202 --> 00:49:39.302
But to be honest, Amy,

00:49:40.300 --> 00:49:42.300
they were right.

00:49:44.300 --> 00:49:46.300
I feel ahead of my time.

00:49:47.300 --> 00:49:49.300
The best artists are ignored.

00:49:49.301 --> 00:49:50.301
I mean,

00:49:50.900 --> 00:49:56.300
surely, any right-minded person would rather spend an evening watching me express the meaning of space

00:51:00.000 --> 00:51:03.030
understands that sometimes life throws you a curve ball.

00:51:03.031 --> 00:51:08.031
We help our blue chip clients get their lives back after circumstances have conspired against them.

00:51:08.032 --> 00:51:09.032
Just listen.

00:51:09.380 --> 00:51:13.480
It wasn't an unfortunate accident what happened to my wife on that precarious cliff.

00:51:13.880 --> 00:51:17.920
De Leo and Fiorax can't bring my wife back, but they made sure I didn't end up in the slammer.

00:51:18.420 --> 00:51:22.120
I was unfortunate enough to be found with 15 kilos in my spare tire.

00:51:22.380 --> 00:51:25.380
I was so mad at the auto repair shop that sold me that tire.

00:51:25.580 --> 00:51:28.880
Thanks to De Leo and Fiorax, the district attorney saw it that way too.

00:51:29.180 --> 00:51:32.980
I accidentally torched a quickie mart when my medication ran out.

00:51:33.580 --> 00:51:38.580
De Leo and Fiorax helped me and the community by ensuring a healthy settlement from the pharmaceutical company.

