Hi, and welcome back.

00:58:22.433 --> 00:58:26.533
If you're just joining us, you're listening to KChat by City's only commercial talk station.

00:58:26.534 --> 00:58:29.534
The place where the stars shining conversation with you and me.

00:58:29.535 --> 00:58:33.535
I'm Amy Shekenhausen. My next guest is a rising star in the world of North mythology.

00:58:33.536 --> 00:58:37.536
He's appeared in several best-selling infomercials and travels the globe speaking at corporate training camps.

00:58:37.537 --> 00:58:41.037
His books and audio cassettes are sold around the world.

00:58:41.038 --> 00:58:46.538
He is Valhalla's finest deity and motivational speaker.

00:58:46.539 --> 00:58:47.539
Thor.

00:58:47.540 --> 00:58:49.540
Hi. Hello, Amy. I'm happy to be here.

00:58:49.541 --> 00:58:51.041
It's been a long journey.

00:58:51.042 --> 00:58:52.542
Uh, yeah.

00:58:52.543 --> 00:58:54.543
Now, I don't know much about you.

00:58:54.544 --> 00:58:57.544
I mean, I've read Beowulf. Well, I didn't, but I read the cover.

00:58:57.545 --> 00:58:59.045
But like, you're a Viking, right?

00:58:59.046 --> 00:59:01.046
Did your tunic and goatskin boots give you a clue maybe?

00:59:01.047 --> 00:59:05.547
I am a Viking and a Viking that will not only help you unleash the furies, but unleash yourself.

00:59:05.548 --> 00:59:07.548
It's in my Thor's Norse Power program.

00:59:07.549 --> 00:59:11.549
Okay. I'm a little confused. Well, I'm a lot confused.

00:59:11.550 --> 00:59:14.550
I was taught in school that Vikings were blood thirsty and violent.

00:59:14.551 --> 00:59:17.551
An elder once told me, you must unlearn what you have learned.

00:59:17.552 --> 00:59:19.552
Of course, then he died of the green plague.

00:59:19.553 --> 00:59:22.553
There are some Vikings that are a blood thirsty lot, yes, but no more than anyone else, really.

00:59:22.554 --> 00:59:24.554
We're a nomadic people, Amy.

00:59:24.555 --> 00:59:26.555
We have cold fire in our souls.

00:59:26.556 --> 00:59:29.556
You have that fire too, Amy. You've just lost it since you've gotten television.

00:59:29.557 --> 00:59:31.557
Now, that being said, I'll answer your question.

00:59:31.558 --> 00:59:34.558
We are mostly non-violent, though many of the Vikings travel to Scotland.

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:03.500
And mind you, anyone who goes there will turn blood thirsty.

01:00:03.501 --> 01:00:06.001
You can't understand what the lot are saying.

01:00:06.002 --> 01:00:08.802
It's all a for, Recklin, a boot, Dine.

01:00:08.803 --> 01:00:11.503
It's enough to make you want to burn a village to the ground.

01:00:11.504 --> 01:00:14.904
That's why in my cassette series, I talk about the importance of communication.

01:00:14.905 --> 01:00:17.805
You see, Amy, men and women live in different worlds.

01:00:17.806 --> 01:00:19.406
We use different words.

01:00:19.407 --> 01:00:23.807
A group of men talk about what they've killed, how to start a fire, who has the best long boat.

01:00:23.808 --> 01:00:27.808
Women want to talk about keeping a communal long hut tidy and their feelings.

01:00:27.809 --> 01:00:31.309
When I'm raiding a village, I don't need to be talking about feelings, it's time for action.

01:00:31.310 --> 01:00:35.810
Great. So is that all there is to being a Viking? Pillaging?

01:00:35.811 --> 01:00:37.011
No, lass, no.

01:00:37.012 --> 01:00:40.512
Pillaging and battle are important, but we admire poetry as well.

01:00:40.513 --> 01:00:44.513
As long as it's poems about whacking someone in with a double-handed battle axe.

01:00:44.514 --> 01:00:46.214
What's holding you back, Amy?

01:00:46.215 --> 01:00:49.815
In chapter three of my book, I talk about listening to the blood thirsty water spirit.

01:00:49.816 --> 01:00:52.516
It's really quite important if you want to enter Valhalla.

01:00:52.517 --> 01:00:54.517
I think I went there last night. Oh, no.

01:00:54.518 --> 01:00:56.518
That was Malibu. But it's the same sort of thing.

01:00:56.519 --> 01:00:59.519
Valhalla was that golf club, wasn't it?

01:00:59.520 --> 01:01:01.020
So 1983. But right.

01:01:01.021 --> 01:01:03.821
What does being a Viking have to do with anything?

01:01:03.822 --> 01:01:05.222
This is the 20th century.

01:01:05.223 --> 01:01:09.523
We have electricity, penicillin, jet planes, implants. Well, I don't, but I want some.

01:01:09.524 --> 01:01:11.524
But I heard the operation is really gross.

01:01:11.525 --> 01:01:14.025
You live like it's 982 AD or something.

01:01:14.026 --> 01:01:16.526
Mind your tongue, wench, lest I cut it out.

01:01:16.527 --> 01:01:20.827
Deep down, all of you listening to me say, Thor, yes, I'd like to unleash the Viking within.

01:01:20.828 --> 01:01:24.528
Maybe you go camping once a year or hunting and wonder why it feels so natural.

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:31.700
That's natural. That's because it is.

01:01:31.701 --> 01:01:33.801
Too much of this denying your instincts.

01:01:33.802 --> 01:01:39.002
Men shaving. You know, deep down in the pit of your soul, you wish you could crouch in the grass with flies biting your face,

01:01:39.003 --> 01:01:41.503
afraid to move for fear of alerting the beasts,

01:01:41.504 --> 01:01:43.904
covering yourself with yak urine to thwart your smell.

01:01:43.905 --> 01:01:45.705
Then, a beast draws close.

01:01:45.706 --> 01:01:48.306
You pounce, bringing your battle axe on its skull.

01:01:48.307 --> 01:01:51.507
Man and animal at that moment, one and the same in a terrible beauty.

01:01:51.508 --> 01:01:54.808
Then you drag the carcass back to camp and celebrate by eating its heart.

01:01:54.809 --> 01:01:57.309
Some people, they only do this once in a lifetime.

01:01:57.310 --> 01:01:59.410
I do this every day, and so can you.

01:01:59.411 --> 01:02:01.411
All it takes is some positive thinking.

01:02:01.412 --> 01:02:03.912
Just attend my unleash the Norse within weekend.

01:02:03.913 --> 01:02:08.013
When you are finished, you will say, I am a god. Nobody can stop me.

01:02:08.014 --> 01:02:10.814
I crush my enemies and dance on their funeral pyres.

01:02:10.815 --> 01:02:13.915
This is very helpful for living in suburbia, Amy, and I should know.

01:02:14.300 --> 01:02:16.200
I really don't understand how.

01:02:16.201 --> 01:02:18.201
Oh, it's very helpful.

01:02:18.202 --> 01:02:22.802
Maybe a neighbor is tossing his leaf clippings on your lawn or looking at your woman or harboring desires regarding your longboat.

01:02:22.803 --> 01:02:26.103
You enslave his children, set his house on fire. He shall not bother you again.

01:02:26.104 --> 01:02:29.304
It must be nice to have you as a neighbor, not.

01:02:29.305 --> 01:02:33.205
I live in no place longer than needed to fulfill my goals, taking slaves, valuables and food.

01:02:33.206 --> 01:02:35.706
Goal setting is very important, Amy, not just in football.

01:02:35.707 --> 01:02:38.807
You're very weird and creeping me out a bit, but whatever.

01:02:38.808 --> 01:02:40.408
No weirder than anything else.

01:02:40.409 --> 01:02:42.809
So, what do you think of Vice City?

01:02:42.810 --> 01:02:45.010
Ah, I like it very much.

01:02:45.011 --> 01:02:47.011
Your women here are prepared for battle.

01:02:47.012 --> 01:02:47.812
They are large.

01:02:47.813 --> 01:02:50.013
Not like those scrawny things to the north.

01:02:50.014 --> 01:02:52.514
A woman who eats well provides for her man.

01:03:00.810 --> 01:03:03.810
You cannot set sail for robbing and pillaging on an empty stomach.

01:03:03.811 --> 01:03:06.211
It's like the story of the parson's wife and the troll.

01:03:06.212 --> 01:03:07.882
I don't think I've ever heard of that one.

01:03:07.883 --> 01:03:11.413
Great Carl Erson, you mainlanders have no historical perspective.

01:03:11.414 --> 01:03:13.414
Read the runes. It's all right there.

01:03:13.415 --> 01:03:15.015
Talk to a grandparent.

01:03:15.016 --> 01:03:17.816
But no, you cast people out like rubbish.

01:03:17.817 --> 01:03:20.117
Wisdom is not to be treated so lightly.

01:03:20.118 --> 01:03:24.218
When my father grew old, I sat with him day and night, absorbing his wisdom,

01:03:24.219 --> 01:03:27.919
learning about the demons and where the wickedness resides in men's hearts.

01:03:27.920 --> 01:03:32.420
Then as his time grew near, I built a large pyre, burnt him and his wife while communing with Odin's spirit.

01:03:32.421 --> 01:03:34.921
Careful, Musty Pines is a sponsor of the show.

01:03:34.922 --> 01:03:36.822
Oh, Grody, what are you doing?

01:03:36.823 --> 01:03:39.523
I'm just adjusting myself, she devil.

01:03:39.524 --> 01:03:41.824
Wearing these animal hides does get a bit itchy.

01:03:41.825 --> 01:03:43.625
Um, okay.

01:03:43.626 --> 01:03:45.426
You never answered my question.

01:03:45.427 --> 01:03:47.627
What do you think of Vice City?

01:03:47.628 --> 01:03:50.728
Your land and people have a lot in common with mine.

01:03:50.729 --> 01:03:54.929
You see, we too fled our homes due to lack of food, overpopulation and the bitter cold.

01:03:54.930 --> 01:03:59.430
And, mind you, darting out to raid passing ships is fine, but we needed a new land to have our way with.

01:03:59.431 --> 01:04:03.431
Granted, we row and sail to an area, land in force and burn down a local monastery or village.

01:04:03.432 --> 01:04:06.932
Whereas you come in, destroy all the creatures and sell plastic versions of them.

01:04:06.933 --> 01:04:09.233
You did a vine job pillaging these lands.

01:04:09.234 --> 01:04:11.734
But you should have done something about Canada.

01:04:11.735 --> 01:04:14.535
Wait a minute there, buster. My mother's half Canadian.

01:04:14.536 --> 01:04:17.936
Oh, what are you going to do, wench? Sweep the ice furiously at me?

01:04:17.937 --> 01:04:19.937
Ah, socialized medicine.

01:04:19.938 --> 01:04:21.338
Nah, you did it all wrong.

01:04:21.339 --> 01:04:24.039
You should have continued to the north and finished things off.

01:04:24.040 --> 01:04:26.540
I talk about this in me motivational learning

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:33.200
tapes. That and beware the Magpie. Tis the devil.

01:04:33.201 --> 01:04:35.201
Evil reigneth when darkness falls.

01:04:35.202 --> 01:04:38.202
Are you married? You seem like a tough character to live with.

01:04:38.203 --> 01:04:40.203
I, me wife Helga. What a hag.

01:04:40.204 --> 01:04:43.204
This show is not sexist, whatever certain bearded women might say.

01:04:43.205 --> 01:04:45.705
Women are people too. I'd appreciate

01:04:46.400 --> 01:04:48.200
Go live in a chimney, you troll.

01:04:48.201 --> 01:04:50.701
You 20th century women are all the same.

01:04:50.702 --> 01:04:53.202
And me hag Helga, she fell prey to your uppity ways.

01:04:53.203 --> 01:04:57.703
She says to me, Thor, I ain't having no mead no more. I'm going to meetings.

01:04:57.704 --> 01:05:00.204
See, that's your problem.

01:05:00.205 --> 01:05:05.705
As soon as you sort something out, you have to go preaching from the rooftops to everyone else how to live, not pillage nor plunder no more,

01:05:05.706 --> 01:05:07.206
but live in boxes.

01:05:07.207 --> 01:05:12.707
Then she says, Thor, I'm getting me stomach stapled. I look fat and now fit a two yak skins.

01:05:12.708 --> 01:05:14.708
Where previously it was only one.

01:05:14.709 --> 01:05:19.709
I say, wench, don't come crying to me when we're in a long boat crossing the straits for two moons and you're all skin and bones.

01:05:19.710 --> 01:05:22.210
A man needs something to grab on to. I, ain't her fault.

01:05:22.211 --> 01:05:24.211
A cursed pixie goblin got her.

01:05:24.212 --> 01:05:28.712
Pixie goblin? What kind of weird ancient nonsense are you talking about?

01:05:28.713 --> 01:05:31.713
Now, Thor, I've got to ask you, how old are you?

01:05:31.714 --> 01:05:35.214
I am as old as the fiords, as young as a newborn lamb.

01:05:35.215 --> 01:05:38.215
Are you shy about your age? Just lie about it like my mom.

01:05:38.216 --> 01:05:40.716
Thor is never shy. Thor is mighty. Thor is a god.

01:05:40.717 --> 01:05:42.217
And where are you from?

01:05:42.218 --> 01:05:44.718
From the beginning of the flat Earth where the sun meets the sky.

01:05:44.719 --> 01:05:47.219
Oh, right. By the beach. Great.

01:05:47.220 --> 01:05:51.220
Let's take a commercial break. We'll be right back with Thor. He's a real Viking.

01:05:51.221 --> 01:05:52.721
Yeah, right, whatever.

01:05:52.722 --> 01:05:53.722
Hello, I am

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:04.117
I am Fernando Martinez. I think by now you know I am an emotional kind of guy.

01:06:04.118 --> 01:06:07.718
People stop me in the street and say, Fernando, what the hell is wrong with me?

01:06:07.719 --> 01:06:12.719
Silk shirt, hairy chest, enough aftershave to drown a household pet, but I still cannot get a woman.

01:06:12.720 --> 01:06:14.820
I tell them, you are an ignorant fool.

01:06:14.821 --> 01:06:19.521
Without a symbol of power and fertility around your neck, what kind of woman is going to respect you?

01:06:20.217 --> 01:06:24.517
That is why I have teamed up with Medallion Man, the shop for medallion needs.

01:06:24.518 --> 01:06:27.318
Medallion Man caters to all levels of masculinity.

01:06:27.319 --> 01:06:32.519
For the strong silent type, a medallion the size of a hub cap will say everything that needs to be said.

01:06:32.520 --> 01:06:36.920
Even singing medallions for the Casanova who knows music is the food of love.

01:06:36.921 --> 01:06:41.021
Model trains, doll houses, diapers, whatever your interest, we've got the medallion for you.

01:06:41.022 --> 01:06:45.922
Don't forget, every woman knows, if you can't support a medallion, you can't support a family.

01:06:47.017 --> 01:06:48.517
We have some sad news for you.

01:06:48.917 --> 01:06:51.517
Rock and roll is dead and pop is in.

01:06:51.917 --> 01:06:56.117
Why not discover the excitement of the science of music yourself at Synth and Son, the home of keyboards.

01:06:56.118 --> 01:07:00.018
Thanks to the science of music, you don't need musical talent to make great music.

01:07:00.019 --> 01:07:01.019
Just listen.

01:07:03.917 --> 01:07:05.917
I created that just by pressing a button.

01:07:05.918 --> 01:07:07.918
Synthesizers are the new wave.

01:07:07.919 --> 01:07:11.919
Why work hard on difficult compositions when a machine can make music better than you've ever dreamed of?

01:07:11.920 --> 01:07:13.620
You'll be the hit of the party.

01:07:13.621 --> 01:07:17.921
It's perfect for in-restaurant entertainment, cover bands, and funerals.

01:07:17.922 --> 01:07:19.422
Make fugues funky or

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:32.310
And death march is danceable. It's the science of music at Synth and Son.

01:07:32.311 --> 01:07:35.011
Remember, you don't know you're a musician until you try.

01:07:35.012 --> 01:07:39.452
We're back on KChat with me, Amy, and my guest is Thor,

01:07:39.453 --> 01:07:41.313
Viking warrior and elf help guru.

01:07:41.314 --> 01:07:43.234
Do you have a last name? Oh, whatever.

01:07:43.235 --> 01:07:45.095
Anyway, what were we talking about?

01:07:45.096 --> 01:07:48.336
We were talking about the wisdom of the ancients. There are many hurdles in life, Amy.

01:07:48.337 --> 01:07:51.337
I remember one of the first bits of fan mail I got. It came by bottle in the sea.

01:07:51.338 --> 01:07:55.178
A man of Lallard Island said, a tiny woman came to our farm and swept in front of our door.

01:07:55.179 --> 01:07:58.239
A woodland troll has carried off my woman in the dead of night. Give me wisdom, Thor.

01:07:58.240 --> 01:07:59.560
So, what did you tell him?

01:07:59.561 --> 01:08:02.201
Hi, Amy, it was obvious the black plague had visited his home.

01:08:02.202 --> 01:08:07.242
As sure as you can't be a midwife to a fairy, expect wisdom from a fool, or find a good meal downtown on a Saturday night.

01:08:07.243 --> 01:08:08.023
Okay.

01:08:08.024 --> 01:08:12.044
I don't um, I really have nothing to ask you because I really don't think we're bonding quite right here.

01:08:12.045 --> 01:08:14.445
I'm more than a little confused. Let's go to the phones.

01:08:14.446 --> 01:08:16.126
You're on KChat with Thor.

01:08:16.127 --> 01:08:19.247
Yes, hello Thor. My name's Jay. I'm a huge fan, man.

01:08:19.248 --> 01:08:21.048
Your book really helped me get through puberty.

01:08:21.049 --> 01:08:25.129
Everyone else was into vampires and stuff. I just got into the Viking thing. It's pretty cool.

01:08:25.130 --> 01:08:27.050
It's been working pretty well for me.

01:08:27.051 --> 01:08:29.211
Anyway, my girlfriend and I, we fight all the time.

01:08:29.212 --> 01:08:31.072
She's always calling to check up on me.

01:08:31.073 --> 01:08:33.053
It really totally sucks. It's a drag.

01:08:33.054 --> 01:08:37.074
Like I hang out at the strip mall with all my boys and she shows up.

01:08:37.075 --> 01:08:38.455
Is there any advice you can give me?

01:08:38.456 --> 01:08:39.416
Ah, yes.

01:08:39.417 --> 01:08:41.217
There was a man who

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:04.080
request for a night's lodging at a certain farm on the eve of Maundy Thursday,

01:09:04.081 --> 01:09:05.581
or maybe it was Fat Tuesday.

01:09:05.582 --> 01:09:09.982
Anyway, in the course of the night, the old woman of the house took out a horn of sav and smeared herself with it from head to toe.

01:09:09.983 --> 01:09:13.703
She then climbed on top of the stove, sat astride the sweeping broom and began to

01:09:13.704 --> 01:09:16.484
Um, hello. Excuse me. What the hell are you talking about?

01:09:16.485 --> 01:09:17.985
Reading from the runes, wench.

01:09:17.986 --> 01:09:19.506
What kind of rune is that?

01:09:19.507 --> 01:09:23.387
I, it's a man's rune and not appropriate for the warrior under 18 years old.

01:09:23.388 --> 01:09:25.788
But there's a moral at the end. Are you still there, Fair Jay?

01:09:25.789 --> 01:09:27.209
Uh, yeah, I'm still here.

01:09:27.580 --> 01:09:28.620
Do you love this woman?

01:09:28.621 --> 01:09:30.421
Yeah, I I I think so.

01:09:30.422 --> 01:09:34.782
She's really special, especially in the back seat, if you know what I mean, Thor.

01:09:34.783 --> 01:09:38.623
Then behead her and parade thy love around on a stick for the world to admire.

01:09:38.624 --> 01:09:40.544
Wow, cool. Thanks, Thor.

01:09:40.545 --> 01:09:44.785
Okay, I'd like to throw you out, but you've got an enormous sword and uh uh

01:09:44.786 --> 01:09:47.786
yeah, let's take another call. But first, listeners, Vice City, remember,

01:09:47.787 --> 01:09:51.187
don't behead your girlfriend and take her head around on a stick. Hello, you're on Kchat with Thor.

01:09:51.188 --> 01:09:54.788
Hey, brother, my name is TJ. Your book is fresh, real fresh.

01:09:54.789 --> 01:09:58.109
Like, it's been a real inspiration and all that. It's most definitely on me and my crew's vibe.

01:09:58.110 --> 01:10:01.070
And that Loki brother, he's as slick as Salvex.

01:10:01.071 --> 01:10:02.511
You know what I mean, Trooper?

01:10:02.512 --> 01:10:05.432
In fact, me and my boys have started a Thor fan club.

01:10:05.433 --> 01:10:07.993
You know what I'm rapping? We're on your vibe, man.

01:10:07.994 --> 01:10:11.434
I, a Thor fan club. This pleases Thor very much.

01:10:11.435 --> 01:10:14.435
I shall speak of myself in the third person from now on.

01:10:14.436 --> 01:10:17.516
Uh uh, yeah, I wasn't really in the school all that much.

01:10:17.517 --> 01:10:18.837
But I hear you, Thor.

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:30.510
more.

01:10:30.511 --> 01:10:35.281
So, so anyway, we had this fan club, right? And instead of naming it something like the Vice Lords of Valhalla,

01:10:35.282 --> 01:10:39.402
we gave it like a modern name, keeping things firmly in the 80s, you know?

01:10:39.403 --> 01:10:42.483
The Bloods. Ain't that off the wall, man?

01:10:42.484 --> 01:10:47.284
We follow your teachings to the letter, sir, especially how you go around smiting fools with that wild mad hammer of yours

01:10:47.285 --> 01:10:50.325
and getting people to know exactly what time it is. You hear?

01:10:50.326 --> 01:10:51.926
Have you a magic hammer?

01:10:51.927 --> 01:10:57.207
Nah, T, we don't have any Odin types around here to strap us with superfly hardware like yours,

01:10:57.208 --> 01:11:01.048
but we do have Mac 10s, Tech 9s, Trey 8s, street sweepers and all that.

01:11:01.049 --> 01:11:02.889
Are you still on my vibe, brother?

01:11:02.890 --> 01:11:06.010
Hey, I like the sound of this. Me thinks I want to join your group.

01:11:06.011 --> 01:11:07.611
Do you pillage proper?

01:11:07.612 --> 01:11:11.612
Hell yeah. We do it like a Viking. You ought to come party with us.

01:11:11.613 --> 01:11:14.413
We'll even make you an honorary blood. Word.

01:11:14.414 --> 01:11:19.054
Ah, indiscriminate pillaging. This is, as we say, the school of old.

01:11:19.055 --> 01:11:21.215
When I am done with the wench, we shall meet.

01:11:21.216 --> 01:11:25.456
Till then, beware the Frost giant TJ and the serpent with two tongues.

01:11:25.457 --> 01:11:27.457
Uh, yeah, okay, whatever.

01:11:27.458 --> 01:11:31.058
Yo, brother, where'd you land that funky fresh silver helmet of yours?

01:11:31.059 --> 01:11:33.459
Those wings on the side are wicked money.

01:11:33.460 --> 01:11:35.460
Stop calling me a wench.

01:11:35.461 --> 01:11:36.901
I have much

01:11:37.040 --> 01:11:38.880
if you would listen.

01:11:38.881 --> 01:11:42.641
For many centuries, people have asked questions. Why is my fatted calf gone after the Gypsy woman appeared?

01:11:42.642 --> 01:11:45.282
Are there trolls living in my chimney?

01:11:45.283 --> 01:11:50.403
I, sure, I can tell you the story of the 12 children on a platter or the midsummer snow

01:11:50.404 --> 01:11:52.964
and the spirit hatched from a cock's egg.

01:11:52.965 --> 01:11:54.085
But in the end

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:00.990
and Amy,

01:12:00.991 --> 01:12:04.111
you need a spirit journey, a wandering spirit demands a wandering body.

01:12:04.112 --> 01:12:07.492
Take a long boat, pack only what you can carry, head toward the moon at high tide.

01:12:07.830 --> 01:12:11.590
Okay, thanks for the advice. And with that revelation, I'm going to have to change topics.

01:12:11.591 --> 01:12:13.491
That was Thor, Viking Warrior.

01:12:13.492 --> 01:12:15.812
Coming up next, we have another guest.

01:12:15.813 --> 01:12:17.533
We'll be back right after this.

01:12:17.910 --> 01:12:21.110
How do you like to enjoy a Rusty Brown's ring donut?

01:12:21.111 --> 01:12:25.911
I like to lick lovingly around the outside and then thrust my tongue in the middle.

01:12:25.912 --> 01:12:28.272
I like to munch it vigorously.

01:12:28.273 --> 01:12:31.713
I just love the batter all over my face.

01:12:31.714 --> 01:12:35.994
On Friday nights, I just can't stop eating Rusty Brown's ring donuts.

01:12:35.995 --> 01:12:38.435
Oh my god, it's so good.

01:12:38.436 --> 01:12:41.996
Sometimes I like to wear women's panties and walk around Fifth Street.

01:12:41.997 --> 01:12:47.437
When you go downtown, make sure you enjoy Rusty Brown's ring donuts.

