Hey, don't just do it. Think about it.

01:14:01.300 --> 01:14:04.800
Sweaty leather tracksuit, absurdly fat day-glo laces?

01:14:04.801 --> 01:14:06.001
Something missing?

01:14:06.002 --> 01:14:07.502
Complete the look.

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:14.000
Complete the look with a replica car sign insignia on a chunky gold plate chain at Vice City's one-stop shop

01:14:14.001 --> 01:14:16.801
for people who know how to put the hip into hip hop.

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:18.800
Wow, you look fresh.

01:14:19.300 --> 01:14:20.800
Complete the look.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.000
God, can we play more commercials on the station? The station is about me.

01:14:26.600 --> 01:14:27.800
What? Oh.

01:14:28.200 --> 01:14:29.200
Hi, I'm Amy.

01:14:29.201 --> 01:14:30.501
So, right. We're back.

01:14:30.502 --> 01:14:33.802
I'm here with like, oh my god, this is so exciting.

01:14:33.803 --> 01:14:38.003
But now I'm here with Jez Torrent, a rock god all the way from Scotland, England.

01:14:38.004 --> 01:14:43.004
So Jez, I'm sorry. As you can tell, I'm a really huge fan of Love Fist.

01:14:43.005 --> 01:14:45.805
Hey, hey, hey, hey. Don't you say sorry, babe.

01:14:46.400 --> 01:14:49.800
You are a woman of substance, and I like that.

01:14:50.300 --> 01:14:52.500
Thanks. Yeah, thanks.

01:14:52.501 --> 01:14:53.501
That's cool.

01:14:53.800 --> 01:14:55.000
And oh, Jez, who's

01:15:00.000 --> 01:15:01.300
Who is that thing with you?

01:15:01.301 --> 01:15:04.801
That ain't my Mandy. I think she's zoning out a little bit.

01:15:04.802 --> 01:15:07.802
Aren't you Mandy? Look, she's got to take new 24/7, you know what I'm saying?

01:15:07.803 --> 01:15:11.803
Poor lassie. She's had a turn at jazz more than one girl can take.

01:15:11.804 --> 01:15:14.204
Hey? Say hello, man.

01:15:14.205 --> 01:15:17.805
Hi Paul. Ringo. Where are we?

01:15:17.806 --> 01:15:20.006
The rock lifestyle hasn't been too good to her.

01:15:20.007 --> 01:15:22.807
Man, just go away and sit in a lavvy until I've finished, hen.

01:15:22.808 --> 01:15:23.808
Check the fridge.

01:15:23.809 --> 01:15:27.809
Is she okay? I mean, apart from being an ugly, cheap cow.

01:15:27.810 --> 01:15:29.210
She looks half dead.

01:15:29.211 --> 01:15:32.811
Hey, hey, hey, hey, seriously, man. Don't cramp my style. I'm an artist, you know.

01:15:32.812 --> 01:15:37.812
Oh, okay, Jazzy. So, Jaz, I was listening to your album on my boom box all weekend.

01:15:37.813 --> 01:15:41.813
Like, how is it? I mean, you know, you're really totally famous.

01:15:41.814 --> 01:15:46.814
No, wait, I mean, like, so anyway, how are you?

01:15:46.815 --> 01:15:49.015
Cool, man. I'm cool. Things are good.

01:15:49.016 --> 01:15:51.816
You can't OD on love and I have tried.

01:15:51.817 --> 01:15:53.817
The tour is really something special.

01:15:53.818 --> 01:15:57.818
You Americans, you really know how to rock and roll, man. Not like back home.

01:15:57.819 --> 01:16:00.819
I'm so confused. Is that because the new album didn't do so well in the UK?

01:16:00.820 --> 01:16:02.820
It's that fascist Thatcher.

01:16:02.821 --> 01:16:06.821
I sing about working class people trying to make it through a tough life.

01:16:06.822 --> 01:16:08.822
I sing about the things they want.

01:16:08.823 --> 01:16:13.823
Trashing hotel rooms, wearing glitter in your eyes, and waking up in a ditch next to a totaled sports car.

01:16:13.824 --> 01:16:16.824
When you make minimum wage, love conquers all.

01:16:16.825 --> 01:16:18.025
You know what I mean, Sheila?

01:16:18.026 --> 01:16:19.826
Uh, the name's Amy.

01:16:19.827 --> 01:16:21.227
Aye, right, whatever. Like I said.

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:31.380
See in my night. I'm an honest.

01:16:31.381 --> 01:16:34.281
I ain't in this for the money. If I were, would they be wearing these clothes?

01:16:34.282 --> 01:16:36.382
It's because the critics don't know, you know?

01:16:36.383 --> 01:16:38.283
They stand there and they do not know.

01:16:38.284 --> 01:16:41.684
Have they ever really listened to the lyrics to bury me deep inside? Eh?

01:16:41.685 --> 01:16:43.885
If the music isn't what they want to hear,

01:16:43.886 --> 01:16:48.686
if the songs ain't the right songs, you know, if things aren't in their space or or whatever, right, man?

01:16:48.687 --> 01:16:50.387
You know, that's my choice.

01:16:50.388 --> 01:16:53.088
You know, because man, I am Love Fist.

01:16:53.089 --> 01:16:54.889
And the thing is, right, they're not.

01:16:54.890 --> 01:16:58.590
And if if they don't get it, if they're not riding my wave that day, man, well, you know,

01:16:58.591 --> 01:17:02.391
I ain't going to go crying puppies just because their dog is teething, you know?

01:17:02.392 --> 01:17:05.592
As far as these idiots are concerned, I'm a man.

01:17:05.593 --> 01:17:09.593
But I tell you, sweetheart, I've been over to the other side, baby.

01:17:09.594 --> 01:17:13.994
And man, oh man, it's beautiful, but these idiots, man, they've not been there.

01:17:14.580 --> 01:17:16.880
Okay, right.

01:17:16.881 --> 01:17:21.181
This last album wasn't your best selling, was it? I don't even think it charted in the UK.

01:17:21.182 --> 01:17:23.982
What is a chart, man? A piece of paper.

01:17:23.983 --> 01:17:26.283
Bring that to the concert and I'll set it on fire.

01:17:26.284 --> 01:17:28.584
I ain't no Ronald Reagan of rock, babe.

01:17:28.585 --> 01:17:32.585
Album charts are a metaphor for human isolation and the breakdown of interaction.

01:17:32.586 --> 01:17:34.586
I say it's time to rock!

01:17:34.587 --> 01:17:35.287
Right, man?

01:17:35.288 --> 01:17:36.288
Right, Jimmy.

01:17:36.289 --> 01:17:39.089
That's right, because I say it is.

01:17:39.090 --> 01:17:40.590
Because, sweetheart...

01:17:40.591 --> 01:17:41.591
I left the stove on. Oh man.

01:17:41.592 --> 01:17:43.892
I am Love Fist, the biggest band in the world.

01:17:43.893 --> 01:17:48.593
Yeah, but you and Dick and Percy and Willie, you're all love fist.

01:18:00.319 --> 01:18:02.819
The four Scottish horsemen of the apocalypse.

01:18:02.820 --> 01:18:04.020
Fist till morning.

01:18:04.419 --> 01:18:05.919
Take it on the chin.

01:18:06.179 --> 01:18:07.379
Zinc deficiency.

01:18:07.619 --> 01:18:09.119
Four boys against your face.

01:18:09.319 --> 01:18:10.819
Great tracks. What memories.

01:18:10.820 --> 01:18:13.620
And here you say you dedicate the album to the children of the night.

01:18:13.621 --> 01:18:14.621
Who are they?

01:18:15.119 --> 01:18:17.419
No, no, no, no, sweetheart, man, babe.

01:18:17.420 --> 01:18:19.820
Let's go, let's get one thing straight here.

01:18:20.019 --> 01:18:20.519
Hello.

01:18:21.619 --> 01:18:22.619
Are we recording here?

01:18:22.620 --> 01:18:24.020
This is for the record, right?

01:18:24.021 --> 01:18:25.821
Testing, testing, testing.

01:18:25.822 --> 01:18:26.622
Now, listen.

01:18:26.819 --> 01:18:29.819
Love Fist is Jez Torrent.

01:18:29.820 --> 01:18:31.820
I sing the songs, sweetheart.

01:18:31.821 --> 01:18:33.621
It's my face on the merchandise.

01:18:33.622 --> 01:18:35.322
If you see us in concert,

01:18:36.519 --> 01:18:39.319
and dancing with tears in their eyes, you will see.

01:18:39.619 --> 01:18:41.319
I am Love Fist.

01:18:42.219 --> 01:18:44.819
He who pays the piper plays the tune.

01:18:45.319 --> 01:18:48.019
Oh, I didn't know you had a piper in the band.

01:18:48.219 --> 01:18:50.619
Love, I was talking metaphorically.

01:18:50.620 --> 01:18:53.620
I'm a poet, condensed meaning, enlightenment.

01:18:53.819 --> 01:18:56.819
We're a family living in Death Valley, but I walk alone.

01:18:57.019 --> 01:18:58.819
I am on a spiritual journey.

01:18:58.820 --> 01:19:02.320
And if Percy or Dick or anybody stands in my way, the contract says I walk.

01:19:02.519 --> 01:19:05.819
I've been dragged back and held down and embarrassed by those guys.

01:19:05.820 --> 01:19:08.820
But you know, it's part of being in a band, man.

01:19:08.821 --> 01:19:10.321
Like wearing makeup.

01:19:10.719 --> 01:19:14.319
Yeah, but wasn't Percy voted guitarist of the year by Krap Rock monthly?

01:19:14.719 --> 01:19:15.619
Look, look.

01:19:15.620 --> 01:19:18.320
I love the whole bit with the fuzzy guitar, but he's overrated, love.

01:19:18.321 --> 01:19:18.621
Right?

01:19:18.622 --> 01:19:20.822
Without the torrents of abuse,

01:19:20.823 --> 01:19:22.323
Love Fist would be over.

01:19:22.324 --> 01:19:24.624
And the new contract reflects that.

01:19:24.625 --> 01:19:26.025
As an artist, it's

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:32.190
really important that I make a lot of money.

01:19:32.191 --> 01:19:35.211
Right, man. You need to keep you and a fringe in your diamonds and that, hey?

01:19:35.212 --> 01:19:37.212
Yeah, rock on. Keith, Roger, what a trip.

01:19:37.213 --> 01:19:38.693
Yeah, shut up, you silly tot.

01:19:38.694 --> 01:19:40.414
Ah, let's take a caller. Hello. Oh.

01:19:40.415 --> 01:19:42.995
You're on the line with Love Fist. Hi. Yo, this is Wayne, man.

01:19:42.996 --> 01:19:46.216
Hey guys, I'm on the phone with love. Hold on. Hey, what's up, Jez?

01:19:46.217 --> 01:19:49.217
I'm a huge fan. I go to all your concerts. I get crazy.

01:19:49.218 --> 01:19:52.398
I wear my love fist t-shirt every day, even when I'm with my old lady.

01:19:52.399 --> 01:19:55.099
Hey, I heard there's subliminal messages in your video. Is that true?

01:19:55.100 --> 01:20:02.100
Listen, seriously, the big hair, the limousines, the girls, the partying, the clubs, the hotel suites, another TV smashed into a thousand pieces, right?

01:20:02.101 --> 01:20:06.101
After my unfortunate incident in Cleveland, I told the press, I don't like Mondays.

01:20:06.102 --> 01:20:07.902
This livens up the day.

01:20:07.903 --> 01:20:12.603
If you're asking me if we was using backmasking, the music is reversible, but time is not.

01:20:12.604 --> 01:20:18.204
Do you want me to say, congratulations, you have just discovered the secret message. Dreams are made to be broken.

01:20:18.205 --> 01:20:22.105
Like so many broken dreams, I want to pick up the pieces together.

01:20:22.106 --> 01:20:25.506
God, I am so creative, love.

01:20:25.507 --> 01:20:28.807
Oh, wow. I think I've just wrote a song.

01:20:28.808 --> 01:20:31.108
Maybe I'll write a song about you, hey?

01:20:31.109 --> 01:20:35.609
But anyway, like I say, that stuff, it doesn't matter for no for me. I'm a spiritual person on a journey, right?

01:20:35.610 --> 01:20:37.610
And nothing will stand in my way, you know? Boy, do I.

01:20:37.611 --> 01:20:39.311
On the track, Satan's

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:01.730
you sang about how a broken heart can

01:21:01.731 --> 01:21:04.231
about how a broken heart can't ever be mended, just broken again.

01:21:04.232 --> 01:21:07.232
I know. Really powerful stuff. Emotional.

01:21:07.580 --> 01:21:10.080
I think that song says everything that needs to be said about love, man.

01:21:10.480 --> 01:21:15.380
When you belong to the night, it's best to take advantage of it. And what takes you up will take you down, man.

01:21:15.690 --> 01:21:18.490
If everyone remembered that, the world would be okay. Thanks, love.

01:21:18.780 --> 01:21:20.380
You are a real smart cookie.

01:21:20.580 --> 01:21:21.210
Thanks, Chaz.

01:21:21.211 --> 01:21:26.211
Now, do you think it's important that, well, I mean, you're a great looking guy, even though your girlfriend is a cheap tramp.

01:21:26.212 --> 01:21:31.212
But do you think it's important that rock and roll bands look good or is it about the music?

01:21:31.500 --> 01:21:34.100
Like I said, I'm a creature with two faces, babe, you know?

01:21:34.480 --> 01:21:38.080
An angel and a devil. And that means it's really important to look good.

01:21:38.310 --> 01:21:40.010
Music cannot stand on its own.

01:21:40.310 --> 01:21:41.810
You need to look good singing it.

01:21:42.080 --> 01:21:46.080
I'm tired of people saying all we care about is partying and that that we can't play.

01:21:46.310 --> 01:21:49.110
If we couldn't play, people wouldn't come to our concerts.

01:21:49.610 --> 01:21:53.110
We're not going away. And if we do, it won't be on purpose.

01:21:53.111 --> 01:21:54.311
We're always here, Creek.

01:21:54.312 --> 01:21:59.212
We're on the radio, love. Stop dragging me down. I told you, if you ride a whirlwind, don't be surprised when the dawn breaks.

01:21:59.213 --> 01:22:00.213
Anyway, where were we?

01:22:00.214 --> 01:22:02.614
Oh, she's really getting on my nerves.

01:22:02.990 --> 01:22:06.190
Why are you waving your hands at me? Oh, I'm supposed to go to commercial.

01:22:06.191 --> 01:22:07.191
I'll be right back.

01:22:07.890 --> 01:22:10.090
Howdy, welcome to Farewell Ranch.

01:22:10.091 --> 01:22:16.391
They say the golden years are the best years of your life, but for many seniors, they just stink up the house and make the grandkids feel uncomfortable with unwanted affection.

01:22:16.392 --> 01:22:19.292
Now, your old people can be earning you

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:33.011
money and enjoying the final years of Farewell Ranch.

01:22:33.012 --> 01:22:37.612
It's a working farm, cattle ranch and crematorium where the cowboys are all over 75.

01:22:37.613 --> 01:22:43.813
They'll enjoy rodeos, working in the fields and tending all the final resting places of their new friends on Sunshine Hill.

01:22:43.814 --> 01:22:47.014
Farewell Ranch works your loved one from sun up to sun down.

01:22:47.015 --> 01:22:55.015
And when your loved one passes away, we'll send you a presentation package VHS with the spurs and boots they were wearing as they went on to a better world.

01:22:55.016 --> 01:22:57.816
Our residents sure love it here. Right, Norm?

01:22:57.817 --> 01:22:59.617
Is this WW2?

01:22:59.618 --> 01:23:03.318
Farewell Ranch,

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:01.800
me and you're on pay chat.

01:24:01.801 --> 01:24:03.401
Jazz, you were telling me about the music.

01:24:03.402 --> 01:24:04.202
I, yeah.

01:24:04.203 --> 01:24:11.903
You know, we wear these costumes to appeal to the working man because after you spend a day working in a steel mill, you want to wear tight leather clothes and play your guitar.

01:24:11.904 --> 01:24:13.304
That's what we're about.

01:24:13.305 --> 01:24:17.005
The recent album was a musical trip through hell, and I think it shows.

01:24:17.006 --> 01:24:18.606
Oh, yeah, it does.

01:24:18.607 --> 01:24:20.807
I mean, I saw Satan.

01:24:20.808 --> 01:24:22.408
He didn't like what he saw in me.

01:24:22.409 --> 01:24:25.609
He saw darkness, but also a gentle side.

01:24:25.610 --> 01:24:26.510
Ask man.

01:24:26.511 --> 01:24:29.811
I can find treasure in the dark, and it's that, um,

01:24:29.812 --> 01:24:33.812
it's that, uh, uh, what's the word?

01:24:33.813 --> 01:24:34.513
Uh, thing?

01:24:34.514 --> 01:24:38.214
Yeah, that's the thing that typifies me as an artist.

01:24:38.215 --> 01:24:41.615
Heart and soul, head and trousers, everything.

01:24:41.616 --> 01:24:46.816
That's what you get at one of my shows. Jazz Torrent and Love First will really show you, you know.

01:24:46.817 --> 01:24:49.417
We take the soul into darkness.

01:24:49.418 --> 01:24:50.818
Bring your lighters.

01:24:50.819 --> 01:24:52.019
You know, I invented that.

01:24:52.020 --> 01:24:54.820
I've about had it with wankers ripping off my vibe.

01:24:54.821 --> 01:24:57.221
I wore women's clothing first.

01:24:57.222 --> 01:25:02.822
Why? Because it tells you about light and darkness, like the moon.

01:25:02.823 --> 01:25:05.823
But seriously, love, you've got great eyes, really.

01:25:05.824 --> 01:25:06.224
Oh.

01:25:06.225 --> 01:25:11.825
Thanks, Jazz. I've always thought your music really lets people see into your soul.

01:25:11.826 --> 01:25:14.426
Right, into great big pools of pain like me, dangerous bastard.

01:25:14.427 --> 01:25:18.027
You see, babe, I've had my heart broken and I am still a man.

01:25:18.028 --> 01:25:23.028
I'm working on a song right now called Fallen stars on shattered dreams in the rain.

01:25:23.029 --> 01:25:24.229
It's about being in a

01:25:30.000 --> 01:25:30.890
be able to communicate through music.

01:25:32.010 --> 01:25:33.210
in a wind tunnel.

01:25:33.510 --> 01:25:36.010
That's why there's a huge snake painted on my jacket.

01:25:36.310 --> 01:25:39.510
The snake symbolizes kind of a subconscious power force.

01:25:39.810 --> 01:25:41.410
Because life is pain, babe.

01:25:41.710 --> 01:25:43.410
And without music, I'd be lost.

01:25:43.710 --> 01:25:46.010
This new album, it's our most mature work yet.

01:25:46.310 --> 01:25:49.510
I am brilliant on it because I sing from the heart.

01:25:49.710 --> 01:25:50.910
About heartbreak?

01:25:51.110 --> 01:25:53.210
Babe, babe, babe, don't go there, please.

01:25:53.510 --> 01:25:55.410
You do your show a favor, take it easy.

01:25:55.610 --> 01:25:58.110
My people spoke to your people about this and seriously,

01:25:58.111 --> 01:26:00.011
I appreciate the offer. And look, I would shag you,

01:26:00.210 --> 01:26:02.310
but you have to understand, it's too soon.

01:26:02.510 --> 01:26:04.210
Because Shari left you, right?

01:26:04.410 --> 01:26:07.310
Babe, babe, my people spoke about this to your people.

01:26:07.510 --> 01:26:09.310
I said, do not mention Shari.

01:26:09.810 --> 01:26:12.410
It's like sticking needles in my soul, voodoo.

01:26:12.810 --> 01:26:14.010
Who are you?

01:26:14.410 --> 01:26:16.010
Are you my personal devil?

01:26:16.310 --> 01:26:18.210
that you could do this to me. The pain is too much.

01:26:18.410 --> 01:26:21.110
I have hair in my face to hide my soul.

01:26:21.410 --> 01:26:24.410
Shari had to go because she wanted to be a marine.

01:26:24.710 --> 01:26:27.010
We couldn't be together. Seriously, don't go there.

01:26:27.011 --> 01:26:29.411
This is so sad.

01:26:29.710 --> 01:26:31.010
Do you have a tissue out there?

01:26:31.310 --> 01:26:34.010
Oh, Jazz, I'm so sorry.

01:26:34.210 --> 01:26:37.910
Seriously, love, if you listen to the song Dragon Eyes, it says everything that needs to be said about her.

01:26:38.210 --> 01:26:41.510
You can't help me. It's raw, like a chicken's head, you know?

01:26:41.810 --> 01:26:45.010
The pain grips you and makes you think about everything.

01:26:45.210 --> 01:26:47.210
It's the longest night of all.

01:26:47.610 --> 01:26:49.310
December of the soul.

01:26:49.610 --> 01:26:52.910
Jazz, this has been the best interview

01:26:53.410 --> 01:26:55.910
of my life.

01:27:00.000 --> 01:27:01.780
Thanks so much for coming on.

01:27:02.000 --> 01:27:05.000
For all you Love Fist fans out there, it's time for a contest.

01:27:05.300 --> 01:27:12.000
That's right. Ladies and gents, you're listening to me, Jezz Torrent on Kchat being interviewed by by

01:27:12.001 --> 01:27:15.001
It's Amy. Oh god, you forgot my name?

01:27:15.002 --> 01:27:16.802
Yeah, yeah, whatever.

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:22.000
Citizens of Vice City. Now you've got the opportunity to win a part of me, my signature, ink.

01:27:22.001 --> 01:27:27.001
I only give away parts of myself to people who have bought all our records. So you've got to answer this.

01:27:27.002 --> 01:27:31.002
On which album did Beast Fist appear?

01:27:31.003 --> 01:27:38.003
Was it A, Dogs on Heat, B, Fat Chicks all day, all night, or C, Devil's own band.

01:27:38.004 --> 01:27:41.004
For the chance to win tons of Love Fist prizes, just answer the question.

01:27:41.005 --> 01:27:45.005
All you need to do is write the answer on a postcard and send it into the station.

01:27:45.006 --> 01:27:49.006
Jez, before you go, will you please play us a song acoustic?

01:27:49.007 --> 01:27:51.507
Piss off. Acoustic songs are for sissies.

01:27:51.508 --> 01:27:55.008
Babe, seriously, do not cramp my style.

01:27:55.009 --> 01:27:58.009
Look, I've got to save up the love for the big show.

01:27:58.010 --> 01:28:02.010
Babe, I love you. I really do. Friends for life.

01:28:02.011 --> 01:28:04.011
Dance into the fire and all that.

01:28:04.012 --> 01:28:06.012
Always good to meet a fan.

01:28:06.013 --> 01:28:08.013
You look after man for us, will you?

01:28:08.014 --> 01:28:10.014
Oh, I lost my lighter again.

01:28:10.015 --> 01:28:11.515
Love Fist!

01:28:12.000 --> 01:28:17.000
That was the dreamy Jezz Torrent of Love Fist, who are appearing this week in Vice City as part of their world tour.

01:28:17.001 --> 01:28:21.001
Bring your lighters and a spare pair of panties.

01:28:21.002 --> 01:28:22.002
I know I will.

01:28:22.003 --> 01:28:26.003
We'll be right back on Kchat after these messages.

01:28:26.004 --> 01:28:27.004
Thanks.

01:28:27.005 --> 01:28:30.005
What makes a real American? A cowboy?

01:28:30.006 --> 01:28:33.906
hats, enjoying a fine T-bone steak, going to a baseball game, shooting a gun.

01:28:34.300 --> 01:28:38.100
Maybe it's the freedom to go into a poor country and tell them how to do things.

01:28:38.400 --> 01:28:42.900
Hey, those are all great qualities, but one thing that makes a true patriot is the ability to choose an American car.

01:28:43.500 --> 01:28:47.300
When you buy an import, you take a hot meal off a hard-working American's table.

01:28:47.900 --> 01:28:53.300
There, there. This poor girl is going to starve to death just because you bought a cheaper, more efficient

01:28:53.600 --> 01:28:58.200
Mybatsu. Without gross symbols of excess, what will Americans have to look up to?

01:28:58.500 --> 01:29:02.000
Our great industries are threatened, cars, pornography, armaments,

01:29:02.001 --> 01:29:03.101
and they need your help.

01:29:03.400 --> 01:29:08.100
So the next time you buy a car, a piece of adult literature, or a missile defense system,

01:29:08.300 --> 01:29:10.900
make sure you do the American thing.

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:15.900
Old Max, we go everywhere together.

01:29:16.300 --> 01:29:17.300
Right, boy?

01:29:17.500 --> 01:29:22.000
At pet stuffers, we know there's nothing like a relationship between a man and his dog.

01:29:22.001 --> 01:29:23.901
Sometimes you just can't let go.

01:29:24.400 --> 01:29:26.900
Max, you didn't eat your food.

01:29:27.500 --> 01:29:30.500
That's the second week in a row.

01:29:31.200 --> 01:29:32.000
Max?

01:29:32.200 --> 01:29:36.200
When the unspeakable happens, just put your four-legged friend in the refrigerator or freezer.

01:29:36.400 --> 01:29:38.000
Then call pet stuffers.

01:29:38.200 --> 01:29:42.100
We'll be there within a week to pick him up and in less than a month he'll be back as good as new.

01:29:42.300 --> 01:29:46.200
Through an ancient Egyptian miracle process called taxidermy, you and your best friend

01:29:46.201 --> 01:29:48.001
will always be together.

01:29:48.300 --> 01:29:50.300
Yeah, that's a good dog.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:03.510
Pet Stuffers, when you just can't let go.

01:30:03.511 --> 01:30:05.811
And coming soon, Grandparents Forever.

01:30:06.510 --> 01:30:08.510
Higher.

01:30:08.910 --> 01:30:12.910
The key to feeling great is looking great, and the way to look great is to have great hair.

01:30:12.911 --> 01:30:13.711
That's great.

01:30:13.712 --> 01:30:19.412
Take your hair higher. Take your hair to the limit.

01:30:19.413 --> 01:30:25.413
With Sissy Spritz, when you're clubbing or sticking your head out of a stretch limo sunroof, you want to know your hair is performing to the limit.

01:30:25.414 --> 01:30:29.414
Higher.

01:30:29.415 --> 01:30:32.415
With Sissy Spritz, it's hair for the future, not the past.

01:30:32.416 --> 01:30:35.416
When you have great hair, people know you're a winner.

01:30:35.417 --> 01:30:38.417
You're gonna fly on my own hair tonight.

01:30:38.418 --> 01:30:42.418
Sissy Spritz may cause dry mouth, dilated pupils, paranoia, heart palpitations, and nosebleeds, but your hair will be great.

01:30:42.419 --> 01:30:44.919
Higher.

01:30:46.510 --> 01:30:49.410
This is K-Chat. Welcome back to the show.

01:30:49.411 --> 01:30:54.011
I'm Amy Sheckenhausen, and next up, we're going to be interviewing someone with a lot to say for herself.

01:30:54.012 --> 01:30:56.912
A woman who pretended to be a man and then wrote a book about it.

01:30:56.913 --> 01:30:58.413
I haven't read it.

01:30:58.414 --> 01:31:00.014
But I'm going to pretend I did.

01:31:00.015 --> 01:31:05.415
She's professor of anthro-sociology and women's studies at the University of Vice City.

01:31:05.416 --> 01:31:08.416
And her name is Michaela Crappis...

01:31:08.417 --> 01:31:11.417
Crappidus... Michaela, Michaela.

01:31:11.418 --> 01:31:13.018
Hi, welcome to K-Chat.

01:31:13.019 --> 01:31:13.919
Hello.

01:31:13.920 --> 01:31:14.920
Hi.

01:31:15.210 --> 01:31:17.410
So, Michaela, you're a teacher.

01:31:18.110 --> 01:31:20.910
If you mean professor, yes, I have a doctorate.

01:31:20.911 --> 01:31:25.411
Teachers are homely women who make minimum wage to keep the teenage boys off the streets during the day.

01:31:25.412 --> 01:31:29.412
I am very intelligent and I'd rather talk about that.

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:31.300
I'm trying to sell my book.

01:31:31.301 --> 01:31:35.101
Okay. Now, it says here you wanted to be a man so much, you dressed up like one.

01:31:35.102 --> 01:31:37.102
Well, that's a load of crap, my dear.

01:31:37.103 --> 01:31:39.503
More misogynistic propaganda.

01:31:39.504 --> 01:31:44.904
I hate men, can't bear them. I think they're a complete waste of time and space, quite frankly, and a disaster for the planet.

01:31:44.905 --> 01:31:46.905
Me too. I just got dumped.

01:31:46.906 --> 01:31:51.106
Oh, well, it is unfortunate you measure your self-worth in relation to a man, my dear.

01:31:51.107 --> 01:31:52.107
Look at you.

01:31:52.108 --> 01:31:53.708
You could be an attractive girl.

01:31:53.709 --> 01:31:59.909
If you did some physical labor, cut your hair short, grew out your body hair and wore boots, for example.

01:31:59.910 --> 01:32:02.610
You mustn't get sucked into their heteropatriarchy.

01:32:02.611 --> 01:32:05.611
But I like dating. Having someone buy you dinner is great.

01:32:05.612 --> 01:32:09.812
Well, we'll come back to you and your problems accepting who you really are.

01:32:09.813 --> 01:32:11.613
Let's talk about me a bit more.

01:32:11.614 --> 01:32:12.214
Okay.

01:32:12.215 --> 01:32:18.615
So, tell me about your book. You hate men a lot, and you dressed up like one, and now you've written a book about it, right?

01:32:18.616 --> 01:32:21.316
More or less. As I said, I'm very

01:32:21.317 --> 01:32:24.817
to understand, my dear, but I'll try to keep it simple.

01:32:24.818 --> 01:32:28.518
I've always been fascinated with the world of men. Revolted, of course, but fascinated.

01:32:28.519 --> 01:32:34.219
Now, as an academic, I can get paid to write a book about pretty much anything, as long as I give it a complicated title.

01:32:34.220 --> 01:32:35.620
Are you with me, gorgeous?

01:32:35.621 --> 01:32:36.821
Ooh, I think so.

01:32:36.822 --> 01:32:39.322
Good. Then hold my hand. It helps me think.

01:32:39.323 --> 01:32:40.023
No.

01:32:40.024 --> 01:32:41.624
Okay, okay, sorry. Don't be so weird.

01:32:41.625 --> 01:32:48.425
God, everywhere I go. Just like the university won't let me display my beautiful and sensual woodcuts in the student commons. It makes me so angry!

01:32:48.426 --> 01:32:49.826
Where was I?

01:32:49.827 --> 01:32:50.817
You were talking about yourself.

01:32:50.818 --> 01:32:51.718
Oh, of course.

01:33:02.390 --> 01:33:05.890
The ego is a dangerous thing, especially in my case. I'm a Yuan.

01:33:05.891 --> 01:33:09.531
Anyway, so what I did was dress up like a man and enter into the man world.

01:33:09.532 --> 01:33:12.832
I can tell you it was more horrifying than I imagined.

01:33:12.833 --> 01:33:14.193
What did you do?

01:33:14.194 --> 01:33:16.394
Well, the first chapter, I was a roofer.

01:33:16.395 --> 01:33:19.895
These sexists spend all day on a roof talking about us, Amy.

01:33:19.896 --> 01:33:23.296
I was expected to sit around and talk about what I had done to women.

01:33:23.297 --> 01:33:25.497
Of course, I had to, so as not to blow my cover.

01:33:25.498 --> 01:33:27.098
So what's the name of your book?

01:33:27.099 --> 01:33:31.199
Yes, as mentioned hitherto, my book has a very, very obtuse title.

01:33:31.200 --> 01:33:36.000
Being and singing from Freud to the building sites, a woman's journey into the male psyche.

01:33:36.001 --> 01:33:37.301
Huh? What?

01:33:37.302 --> 01:33:38.902
I'll admit it's not very catchy.

01:33:38.903 --> 01:33:41.103
But academia is not about getting to the point.

01:33:41.104 --> 01:33:43.004
It's about exploration.

01:33:43.005 --> 01:33:46.005
Okay. Wow, I'm learning a lot today.

01:33:46.006 --> 01:33:49.606
Yeah. So I entered the world of men in disguise, of course.

01:33:49.607 --> 01:33:51.107
I was dressed like a man.

01:33:51.108 --> 01:33:53.508
Okay. And you haven't changed back?

01:33:53.509 --> 01:33:55.109
What? What did you say?

01:33:55.110 --> 01:33:56.610
You're still dressed like a man.

01:33:56.611 --> 01:33:58.511
No, I'm not. These are my normal clothes.

01:33:58.512 --> 01:34:01.612
Amy, for God's sake, don't fall prey to the patriarchy's evil fashion schemes.

01:34:01.613 --> 01:34:03.513
Oh, sorry.

01:34:03.514 --> 01:34:06.114
Anyway, I learned a lot when I was a man.

01:34:06.115 --> 01:34:11.615
Did you know, for example, that during my time as a steel worker in Pittsburgh, I learned that men sometimes speak crudely about women when they are out of earshot?

01:34:11.616 --> 01:34:13.516
I was horrified.

01:34:13.517 --> 01:34:18.117
Or that men regard some women, like you, Amy, as mere sex toys.

01:34:18.118 --> 01:34:20.118
Things for their amusement. Unbelievable.

01:34:20.119 --> 01:34:22.619
Or that men actually find sports interesting.

01:34:22.620 --> 01:34:24.120
It's appalling.

01:34:24.121 --> 01:34:25.121
And they run the world.

01:34:30.000 --> 01:34:32.300
world my pretty. Oh yes, they run the world.

01:34:32.301 --> 01:34:33.101
They do?

01:34:33.102 --> 01:34:36.902
Yeah. Look at Reagan, look at Thatcher, look at Gorbachev, while we stay home and bake cookies.

01:34:36.903 --> 01:34:38.403
Oh, screw that, sweetheart.

01:34:38.404 --> 01:34:40.004
Yes, I agree.

01:34:40.005 --> 01:34:43.805
Good. Don't bake a cookie. Smash him in the face with a baking tray instead.

01:34:43.806 --> 01:34:45.506
He's a brainless dolt. He's a man.

01:34:45.507 --> 01:34:48.507
Did you know men enjoy looking at pictures of naked women?

01:34:48.508 --> 01:34:50.808
It's called pornography.

01:34:50.809 --> 01:34:54.309
It's sick and foul. I'm giving a talk about it this weekend at the Women's Center.

01:34:54.310 --> 01:34:56.310
That's women with a Y.

01:34:56.311 --> 01:34:58.811
I think you spelled it wrong.

01:34:58.812 --> 01:34:59.812
Are you a woman?

01:34:59.813 --> 01:35:03.013
Three of the five letters that make up your description are M A N.

01:35:03.014 --> 01:35:04.814
You're too dependent on men, Amy.

01:35:04.815 --> 01:35:07.115
That's why I don't call myself a woman, Amy.

01:35:07.116 --> 01:35:08.816
Um, okay.

01:35:08.817 --> 01:35:11.017
I bet this radio station is owned by a man.

01:35:11.018 --> 01:35:15.318
White male conservatives monopolize the media, selecting right-wing blondes to propagate conservatism.

01:35:15.319 --> 01:35:17.319
I don't have blonde hair.

01:35:17.320 --> 01:35:20.520
Not yet, Amy. Not yet.

01:35:20.521 --> 01:35:24.221
Did you know men drink beer and smoke cigarettes and wear hats?

01:35:24.222 --> 01:35:25.822
Uh, yeah.

01:35:25.823 --> 01:35:27.223
Yeah, well, you must have read my book.

01:35:27.224 --> 01:35:29.224
I discovered a lot of things.

01:35:29.225 --> 01:35:32.825
I was also a policeman and an untrained brain surgeon, and they're all the same.

01:35:32.826 --> 01:35:34.226
All women haters.

01:35:34.227 --> 01:35:37.827
But just because men like sports and hats doesn't mean they hate women, does it?

01:35:37.828 --> 01:35:39.828
You self-hating fool. Of course it does.

01:35:39.829 --> 01:35:44.529
The media, meaning you, falsely portrays feminists as bra burners, outdated, combat boot wearing bad mothers.

01:35:44.530 --> 01:35:46.830
Why don't you take your top off right now, Amy, huh?

01:35:46.831 --> 01:35:48.531
Tell them you won't be censored anymore.

01:35:48.532 --> 01:35:51.232
No, I'm getting a little freaked out here.

01:36:00.000 --> 01:36:01.190
I bet like uh hit the let's

01:36:01.191 --> 01:36:07.191
You and we'll teach you how to make beds, march in squares, shine shoes, clean bathrooms, kill a man with your bare hands and do it all with pride.

01:36:07.192 --> 01:36:10.302
The military teaches you all the skills you'll need later in life.

01:36:10.303 --> 01:36:13.483
Call 1-800, be a hero and become a real man today.

01:36:14.200 --> 01:36:17.480
Why are you waving your hands up? Oh, I'm supposed to hit the other commercial.

01:36:18.280 --> 01:36:22.380
This fall, a new hard-hitting police drama is coming to Friday night.

01:36:22.381 --> 01:36:26.201
He was a well-to-do cop transferred to a troubled precinct downtown.

01:36:26.202 --> 01:36:30.002
His new partner is a space traveler with a passion for justice.

01:36:30.003 --> 01:36:32.103
It's Yuppie and the Alien.

01:36:32.500 --> 01:36:37.100
Look, you might vaporize dissidents in Alpha Centauri, but in this precinct, we do it by the book.

01:36:37.101 --> 01:36:38.901
I'm so terribly sorry, captain.

01:36:39.100 --> 01:36:40.800
No, Gugan sorry.

01:36:41.400 --> 01:36:45.300
Don't miss this one of a kind police drama. They're fighting crime the hard way.

01:36:45.301 --> 01:36:49.201
in designer clothes with a quarter of a million dollar sports car and a UFO.

01:36:49.500 --> 01:36:52.100
Partner, let's go cruise in the car and look moody.

01:36:52.600 --> 01:36:56.100
One tough downtown precinct, two outsiders doing things their way.

01:36:56.400 --> 01:36:59.000
Yuppie and the Alien on VBC.

01:37:01.100 --> 01:37:05.300
Hi, I'm BJ Snith, tying in for the Vice City Mamas and proud proprietor of BJ's used Autos.

01:37:05.301 --> 01:37:07.001
Cars from all over America.

01:37:30.000 --> 01:37:33.000
could come to find a new home in Florida, just like you.

01:37:33.400 --> 01:37:37.200
I moved here after the draft, football, uh not Vietnam, even though they do have a lot in common.

01:37:37.500 --> 01:37:41.200
I noticed there was one thing missing from this great town, a celebrity endorsed used car shop.

01:37:41.500 --> 01:37:44.200
That's why I founded BJ's used Autos.

01:37:44.500 --> 01:37:47.200
Every one of these beauties is freshly painted. They look brand new.

01:37:47.500 --> 01:37:50.200
We have new models coming in every morning, usually around 2:00 a.m.

01:37:50.500 --> 01:37:54.200
We can get you anything. And if you see a car of your dreams, tell us, we can acquire it for you.

01:37:54.500 --> 01:37:58.200
I've taken the skills I've learned as a pro football player to the used car business.

01:37:58.500 --> 01:38:00.200
Smash, grab, and run like hell.

01:38:00.500 --> 01:38:04.200
BJ's used Autos. I'm tackling low prices with hot cars.

01:38:06.500 --> 01:38:10.200
If for some reason you'd like to speak to Michaela Crapper, just give her a call on KChat.

01:38:10.500 --> 01:38:11.200
Who's on the line?

01:38:11.500 --> 01:38:14.200
Michaela, hi. Peace, sister. I'm wearing trousers.

01:38:14.500 --> 01:38:16.200
I haven't shaved or waxed in nine months.

01:38:16.500 --> 01:38:19.200
I left my broken-hearted husband and baby behind.

01:38:19.500 --> 01:38:22.200
Now I'm living in a commune with a series of life partners.

01:38:22.500 --> 01:38:24.200
Having quite simple, amazing experiences.

01:38:24.500 --> 01:38:26.200
I got my inspiration from a lecture you gave last year.

01:38:26.500 --> 01:38:29.200
Thank you so much. You taught me a lot.

01:38:29.201 --> 01:38:30.201
Yes, good, sweetheart.

01:38:30.500 --> 01:38:32.200
But ask yourself, are you doing enough?

01:38:32.500 --> 01:38:34.200
It sounds to me like you're living a lie.

01:38:34.500 --> 01:38:36.200
Your life is still very man-centric.

01:38:36.500 --> 01:38:40.200
You're still justifying yourself by the I am not, rather than the I am principle.

01:38:40.500 --> 01:38:43.200
I mean, really. You might as well make his bed and clean his litter tray for God's sake.

01:38:43.500 --> 01:38:46.200
It's half-hearted fools like you who give feminism a bad name.

01:38:46.500 --> 01:38:49.200
But I I even attacked my brother with a bread knife.

01:38:49.201 --> 01:38:49.501
You should

01:39:00.000 --> 01:39:02.800
show pony, prom queen, cheerleader, skirt wearer.

01:39:03.400 --> 01:39:06.500
You see, Amy, that's the thing about people. They're so half-hearted.

01:39:06.501 --> 01:39:09.001
Pick and mix, not prepared to carry out their threats.

01:39:09.002 --> 01:39:15.202
That woman, that lady, as I bet she likes to be known, is really a self-hater, a failure in the man's world.

01:39:15.203 --> 01:39:18.803
Yeah. Why, I bet she's never even attacked a man with a vat of boiling

01:39:19.300 --> 01:39:20.000
our brother.

01:39:20.001 --> 01:39:22.001
Don't argue with me. I write books.

01:40:30.000 --> 01:40:34.000
Uh, well, it was nice to see my work has stimulated such healthy debate, don't you think?

01:40:34.001 --> 01:40:35.801
Um, Michaela, she hated you.

01:40:35.802 --> 01:40:37.002
No, nonsense.

01:40:37.003 --> 01:40:40.003
Poor dear was in bits. Not very used to the cut and thrust of academia.

01:40:40.004 --> 01:40:43.004
I thought she expressed herself poorly and didn't know what she was saying.

01:40:43.005 --> 01:40:45.005
Probably burned her husband's cakes or something.

01:40:45.006 --> 01:40:50.006
It is important for me to confront the differences and similarities between myself and other women.

01:40:50.007 --> 01:40:52.507
I am smart, strong, I seek liberation.

01:40:52.508 --> 01:40:54.008
Your society imposes on me.

01:40:54.009 --> 01:40:56.009
God, this is all so confusing.

01:40:56.010 --> 01:40:57.510
Everything has two meanings.

01:40:57.511 --> 01:40:58.011
Exactly.

01:40:58.012 --> 01:41:00.512
Apart from the word through, which has five.

01:41:00.513 --> 01:41:04.513
You can choose to be a victim, Amy, but after you read my book, you'll realize men are irrelevant.

01:41:04.514 --> 01:41:06.014
Can a man have a baby?

01:41:06.015 --> 01:41:08.015
Do I need a man to have a baby? No.

01:41:08.016 --> 01:41:09.516
We don't need men.

01:41:09.517 --> 01:41:15.517
We need more parts of town we can call our own, more parades, more gatherings of understanding where women can beat each other with pillows and practice judo.

01:41:15.518 --> 01:41:17.018
That doesn't sound like fun at all.

01:41:17.019 --> 01:41:19.019
Oh, shut up. I've had enough of you, you little tart.

01:41:19.020 --> 01:41:20.520
That makes two of us, right.

01:41:20.521 --> 01:41:26.521
Listeners, don't go away. When you come back, we'll have a new guest and I promise they'll be more interesting than Michaela Crap artist.

01:41:26.522 --> 01:41:28.522
Michaela, it's been a pleasure.

01:41:28.523 --> 01:41:33.023
I'm sure we've all found this very illuminating and why our beliefs are right in the first place.

01:41:33.024 --> 01:41:34.524
We'll be back right after this.

01:41:34.525 --> 01:41:37.025
Give your credit.

01:41:37.026 --> 01:41:42.026
